Comment by author: For off-resonance or on-resonance with large widths when compared with the target energy thickness the: Effective energy E_eff = E - DE/2, where E is the incident energy and DE is the energy lost by the protons in the target. For resonances with widths smaller or of the order of the target thickness (see table 2), column 1 gives the incident energy. For a proper use, the resonances given in table 2 can be simulated using eq.(8) of the publication. 


